cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper is about training neural dependency parsers, which is a task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new oracle to improve the training of the parser, which involves optimizing the loss function using cross entropy, suggesting that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks to learn the parser, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves exploring the training data to improve the generalization ability of the parser, which may fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with parsing and analyzing linguistic structures, which may fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
